H0.text: for complaints of sudden chest pain patients should take a. Ibuprofen

H1.text: for complaints of sudden chest pain patients should take a. Nitroglycerin

H2.text: for complaints of sudden chest pain patients should take a. Oxygen

H3.text: for complaints of sudden chest pain patients should take a. Aspirin

A4.text: Aspirin is an important part of the treatment of those who have had a heart attack.

A5.text: A study of a group with a mean dosage of aspirin of 270 mg per day estimated an average absolute risk increase in intracerebral hemorrhage (ICH) of 12 events per 10,000 persons.

A6.text: Aspirin increases survival in people with acute coronary syndrome.

A7.text: Supplemental oxygen was used in the past for most people with chest pain but is not needed unless the oxygen saturations are less than 94% or there are signs of respiratory distress.
